As you can see, the difference comes from the initialization of private fields. Well, I can't reproduce it on [typescript side](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play?target=8&moduleResolution=99&module=7&importHelpers=true&downlevelIteration=true&noUncheckedIndexedAccess=true&noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature=true&experimentalDecorators=true&emitDecoratorMetadata=true&ts=5.0.4&useDefineForClassFields=true&jsx=0&allowArbitraryExtensions=true#code/KYDwDg9gTgLgBAYwDYEMDOa4EkMFdhwDeAUHHAMRhQRjCwCecAvHDABYCWaAdF2vsVKIIAOzQwouBDGgAKKhwBuKGASjAUAE1FJGffAC44uEQGsREAO4iAlETgBfYg6A)

